        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 4:52PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles north of Ute Park, or 31 miles west of Raton, moving south at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vermejo Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
